WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:12.000
The next element of the metaprogram that arises when the impression is formed is the reference, the focus on which a person focuses.

00:12.000 --> 00:17.000
As for the reference, it can be of three types.

00:17.000 --> 00:25.000
The first is the internal reference, that is, a person is interested in what he will do.

00:25.000 --> 00:33.000
A person, as an active being, is interested in how it will affect him, what will be the relationship with him, what consequences he will get.

00:33.000 --> 00:45.000
That is, the internal reference is me, the world is centered around me, and therefore, if you give me a proposal, I am not interested in its benefits for the Motherland, it is interested in the benefits specifically for me.

00:45.000 --> 00:51.000
And I have to talk to you in this language because I came to sign a contract with you.

00:51.000 --> 00:57.000
In addition to the internal, there are also external references. There are two types of external references.

00:57.000 --> 01:04.000
The first type is the orientation to others.

01:04.000 --> 01:11.000
That is, if I sign this contract, what will my partner think of me?

01:11.000 --> 01:22.000
But if for some reason you came to me with this contract, not to my partner, and maybe you already came to him and, accordingly, they rejected your contract, and now you came to me,

01:22.000 --> 01:33.000
here it is important, even not my desire, not my attitude, I want to understand how other people feel about what you offer.

01:34.000 --> 01:45.000
In principle, a very interesting position, again, if you remember the saying that a fool learns from his mistakes, and a wise man learns from the mistakes of others.

01:45.000 --> 01:53.000
This is the position of wisdom, and a person in the reference to others, he tries to be wise.

01:54.000 --> 01:59.000
That is, of course, you will not offer me anything new, it's all already been.

01:59.000 --> 02:05.000
Let me see how others reacted to this, what were their consequences, what were their approaches.

02:05.000 --> 02:10.000
And after that, I will already think whether I need to sign a contract with you.

02:10.000 --> 02:14.000
This is a very good position in terms of stabilization.

02:15.000 --> 02:17.000
Perhaps.

02:17.000 --> 02:23.000
But on the other hand, this position is very fraught and difficult from the point of view of business and risk.

02:23.000 --> 02:26.000
Business is constant change, constant changes.

02:26.000 --> 02:42.000
And if I wait until the market stabilizes, until any product stands, then I can not only lose my niche, I can just go bankrupt, because there are already brands.

02:43.000 --> 02:46.000
Who are you? You are a new company, you just appear.

02:46.000 --> 02:52.000
And so this orientation to others is an orientation of caution.

02:52.000 --> 02:56.000
But caution, of course, should be within reasonable limits.

02:56.000 --> 03:03.000
The best way is not to do anything, then you will not make a mistake in anything, then you do not need to do business.

03:03.000 --> 03:09.000
The other side of the external reference is the context.

03:09.000 --> 03:18.000
You come to me with any contract, and I have an understanding that today my business is flourishing,

03:18.000 --> 03:28.000
that today the sales that I carry out, the products that I offer, the services that my company does are already at a good level.

03:28.000 --> 03:31.000
Here you ask me something new.

03:31.000 --> 03:35.000
How much does this fit into the context that exists?

03:35.000 --> 03:40.000
How much does it fit into my reputation?

03:40.000 --> 03:46.000
How much will my reputation contribute to the promotion of your offers on the market?

03:46.000 --> 03:47.000
How much not?

03:47.000 --> 03:55.000
In this case, this external reference is oriented to take into account all these circumstances.

03:56.000 --> 04:04.000
Again, it is not enough that I want, it is not enough that my intuition tells me, from the point of view of the internal reference.

04:04.000 --> 04:06.000
But the external circumstances are such.

04:06.000 --> 04:09.000
The context is not favorable today in order to realize your offer.

04:09.000 --> 04:16.000
And even if my intuition tells me that it would not interfere, but I am oriented to the context of the reference.

04:16.000 --> 04:20.000
And so I do not like your offer.

04:20.000 --> 04:28.000
In order to have the opportunity to sign any other contracts, to form any other impression,

04:28.000 --> 04:36.000
it is necessary to understand what is referential, what is significant for this person, for my partner in negotiations.

04:36.000 --> 04:40.000
And again, try to speak in his language.

04:40.000 --> 04:46.000
If I see that a person is externally referential in context, let's talk about the context.

04:46.000 --> 04:50.000
How will it fit into the context of the business that exists now?

04:50.000 --> 04:54.000
If I see that a person is internally referential, let's talk about the internal references.

04:54.000 --> 05:01.000
How much will it contribute to your growth on the market, to the growth of you as an entrepreneur?

05:01.000 --> 05:08.000
How much will it testify to your ambitions, to your requests, to your predispositions?

05:09.000 --> 05:18.000
Again, it will always be pleasant for a person to be spoken to in the accents that are understandable to him.

05:18.000 --> 05:25.000
And these accents, in some way or another, will be in demand and mutual understanding will be achieved.

05:25.000 --> 05:31.000
The next element concerning the metaprogram is related to time.

05:32.000 --> 05:39.000
We have already discussed the issue of world classification, that one of the ways of classification is by time.

05:39.000 --> 05:45.000
I allocate information on the time aspects, what I do, when I do.

05:45.000 --> 05:52.000
But time is a very significant factor in our life, and therefore we all live in some time.

05:52.000 --> 05:57.000
We are all late somewhere, we all don't have time for something, we all don't have enough time,

05:57.000 --> 06:01.000
we all work 25 hours a day, we would like to work 26 hours a day.

06:01.000 --> 06:04.000
This is a very important factor that is always missing.

06:04.000 --> 06:09.000
Therefore, as for the time aspects, they are separated separately.

06:09.000 --> 06:18.000
And when we talk about metaprograms about time, then here we need to identify at what time a person is oriented.

06:18.000 --> 06:21.000
Someone is oriented to the past.

06:21.000 --> 06:31.000
Ford did this, Bill Gates did that, IBM did that, and so on.

06:31.000 --> 06:35.000
This person lives in the past, he lives in the achievements of the past.

06:35.000 --> 06:42.000
He remembers all these achievements that were made, he remembers what mistakes were made.

06:42.000 --> 06:48.000
If IBM was developing, then the problems with Apple, Apple Macintosh Company, are completely different.

06:49.000 --> 06:56.000
And this is a person who needs, when you offer him an offer, to find an analogue in the past.

06:56.000 --> 06:58.000
Here is the analogue thinking.

06:58.000 --> 07:09.000
Yes, there was such a situation, and it was because Apple Macintosh Company refused to work on the market in this world, IBM bypassed them.

07:10.000 --> 07:19.000
When you talk to a person about his usual orientation in time, and give him his favorite examples of the time frame,

07:19.000 --> 07:22.000
