10:04.000 --> 10:07.000
he is not interested, because he has problems now.

10:07.000 --> 10:11.000
The time orientation is really very painful,

10:11.000 --> 10:15.000
just because there are all-time problems that need to be solved,

10:15.000 --> 10:17.000
and you take my time.

10:17.000 --> 10:20.000
In principle, you need to understand these issues.

10:20.000 --> 10:25.000
If you enter the same time orientation with a person,

10:25.000 --> 10:30.000
then you are very close to getting contacts and interactions with him.

10:30.000 --> 10:35.000
But in addition to the orientation of the past-present-future or the timeline,

10:35.000 --> 10:38.000
there is also such an aspect as the duration of time.

10:38.000 --> 10:42.000
People differ in their attitude to time.

10:42.000 --> 10:47.000
Someone lives in time,

10:47.000 --> 10:51.000
that is, he always knows how much time is now,

10:51.000 --> 10:57.000
he always controls how much time he needs to get somewhere,

10:57.000 --> 11:00.000
how much time is left to complete the annual report,

11:00.000 --> 11:05.000
how much time should pass until you send me the necessary information.

11:05.000 --> 11:13.000
This is a person who lives in so-called through time.

11:13.000 --> 11:19.000
In the course of time, a person constantly controls the time he has.

11:19.000 --> 11:25.000
This person is pedantic, scrupulous, punctual.

11:25.000 --> 11:29.000
This is what is called the accuracy and politeness of kings.

11:29.000 --> 11:32.000
For him, if you come to a contract,

11:32.000 --> 11:36.000
we say that within a year we will get such results.

11:36.000 --> 11:38.000
These are not words.

