01:00:11.000 --> 01:00:15.000
let's take a statement, which, again, can be often encountered,

01:00:15.000 --> 01:00:22.000
that we cannot refuse to work with the previous provider,

01:00:22.000 --> 01:00:25.000
and it is not profitable to work with several.

01:00:25.000 --> 01:00:28.000
Again, you make some offer,

01:00:28.000 --> 01:00:31.000
you have already formed a company,

01:00:31.000 --> 01:00:34.000
and very often such an argument can be made.

01:00:34.000 --> 01:00:37.000
Then you can ask the following question,

01:00:37.000 --> 01:00:39.000
what exactly is preventing you?

01:00:39.000 --> 01:00:44.000
Who said that you cannot work with another provider?

01:00:44.000 --> 01:00:49.000
And what will happen if you refuse to work with us?

01:00:49.000 --> 01:00:53.000
What will happen if you refuse to work with the providers

01:00:53.000 --> 01:00:55.000
who you are working with now?

01:00:55.000 --> 01:00:57.000
Are you satisfied with everything?

01:00:57.000 --> 01:00:59.000
Has he ever let you down?

01:00:59.000 --> 01:01:02.000
We ask questions and try to find the ground,

01:01:02.000 --> 01:01:05.000
the ground for conversation, the ground for mutual understanding,

01:01:05.000 --> 01:01:08.000
the ground for the conversation to continue,

01:01:08.000 --> 01:01:11.000
because if we are told that we cannot work,

01:01:11.000 --> 01:01:14.000
then the conversation ends on its own.

01:01:14.000 --> 01:01:18.000
Now we are trying to find the common points of contact,

01:01:18.000 --> 01:01:24.000
because these points of contact will allow us to further develop the topic,

01:01:24.000 --> 01:01:28.000
to master the metaprograms, to master this or that information,

01:01:28.000 --> 01:01:33.000
to work with specific verbs and statements.

01:01:33.000 --> 01:01:38.000
Model operators are used quite often,

01:01:38.000 --> 01:01:47.000
and in fact they are a reflection of the experience I had,

01:01:47.000 --> 01:01:51.000
the experience I had, the experience I worked with, the experience I am based on.

01:01:51.000 --> 01:01:56.000
Our task is to shake up this negative sensory experience

01:01:56.000 --> 01:01:59.000
that I got through my sensory organs,

01:01:59.000 --> 01:02:02.000
maybe I got some bumps on it,

01:02:02.000 --> 01:02:05.000
but it was, and it was not with me.

01:02:05.000 --> 01:02:07.000
Now the situation has changed.

01:02:07.000 --> 01:02:15.000
Let's do some actions that will allow you to dispel the difficulties that arise in me.

01:02:15.000 --> 01:02:20.000
The question of majority often arises with children, with parents,

01:02:20.000 --> 01:02:23.000
with employees.

01:02:23.000 --> 01:02:26.000
As for HR, it is very often said here,

01:02:26.000 --> 01:02:28.000
you must come to work on time,

01:02:28.000 --> 01:02:31.000
you must work until you do everything.

01:02:31.000 --> 01:02:33.000
Who am I supposed to work with? Who said that?

01:02:33.000 --> 01:02:35.000
What will happen if I don't do it?

01:02:35.000 --> 01:02:40.000
Very often these problems, these model operators lead to conflicts,

01:02:40.000 --> 01:02:43.000
they form an authoritarian impression

01:02:43.000 --> 01:02:48.000
that has no effect on the image, brand, reputation of the company.

01:02:48.000 --> 01:02:50.000
You have to work with them,

01:02:50.000 --> 01:02:55.000
because in fact they are very easily shaken up and very easily changed.

01:02:55.000 --> 01:03:03.000
But this is not all that can be faced from the point of view of the verbality of the formation of the correct impression.

01:03:03.000 --> 01:03:09.000
The next verbal characteristic that very often contributes to the formation of an inadequate impression

01:03:09.000 --> 01:03:13.000
is the use of the universal quantitative.

01:03:13.000 --> 01:03:20.000
Many, all, never, always, the slogan from the 12th studio.

01:03:20.000 --> 01:03:28.000
Universal quantitative is just a quantity that has no clear values.

01:03:28.000 --> 01:03:32.000
Accordingly, when we try to clarify,

01:03:32.000 --> 01:03:36.000
we must ask a question about how to concretize the above statement.

01:03:36.000 --> 01:03:41.000
Universal quantitative is always a super-comprehension.

01:03:41.000 --> 01:03:45.000
We generalize everything in one way or another.

01:03:45.000 --> 01:03:48.000
In this regard, what can we do?

01:03:48.000 --> 01:03:55.000
For example, to repeat the same universal quantitative that you gave me in a questionable form.

01:03:55.000 --> 01:04:01.000
Well, in the traditional statement, especially for women,

01:04:01.000 --> 01:04:03.000
all men are greedy.

01:04:03.000 --> 01:04:06.000
Indeed, here is a very important question.

01:04:06.000 --> 01:04:10.000
Indeed, all your husbands are greedy, your boss is greedy.

01:04:10.000 --> 01:04:15.000
Every man who was greedy at the beginning of his life, your parents were greedy.

01:04:15.000 --> 01:04:18.000
There is, of course, a certain subtlety,

01:04:18.000 --> 01:04:22.000
because you can get to such an example that confirms once again.

01:04:22.000 --> 01:04:27.000
But again, in this situation, you do not need to touch on significant examples,

01:04:27.000 --> 01:04:30.000
but you need to take something neutral.

01:04:30.000 --> 01:04:37.000
For example, you cannot remember a single man who was generous.

01:04:37.000 --> 01:04:40.000
Santa Claus can always be remembered.

01:04:40.000 --> 01:04:43.000
Of course, he is generous, he has his own generosity.

01:04:43.000 --> 01:04:46.000
What exactly are men greedy?

01:04:46.000 --> 01:04:49.000
What do you understand by the greed of a man?

01:04:49.000 --> 01:04:52.000
Look, there is a universal quantitative,

01:04:52.000 --> 01:04:55.000
all men with the same success can be called women.

01:04:55.000 --> 01:04:58.000
I would like to ask the same question.

01:04:58.000 --> 01:05:01.000
All, all, all, really?

01:05:01.000 --> 01:05:03.000
So that a person thinks,

01:05:03.000 --> 01:05:08.000
does it really make sense for him to make this statement now,

01:05:08.000 --> 01:05:11.000
if you say that your boss is a man,

01:05:11.000 --> 01:05:15.000
and you are discussing with him the issue of raising your salary?

01:05:15.000 --> 01:05:21.000
Another way is to thicken the paints even more.

01:05:21.000 --> 01:05:25.000
For example, no one knows the drug Propylex.

01:05:25.000 --> 01:05:27.000
No one knows at all.

01:05:27.000 --> 01:05:32.000
If no one knew Propylex, how would he take any other thing on the market?

01:05:32.000 --> 01:05:37.000
Who exactly does not know anything about Propylex?

01:05:37.000 --> 01:05:39.000
And the same person will think,

01:05:39.000 --> 01:05:42.000
so, will I not expose myself in a bad light,

01:05:42.000 --> 01:05:45.000
if I say that no one knows about it,

01:05:45.000 --> 01:05:48.000
or maybe only I do not know about it?

01:05:48.000 --> 01:05:54.000
Another way is to get an exceptional example from the interlocutor.

01:05:54.000 --> 01:05:58.000
Again, the examples we talked about were there.

01:05:58.000 --> 01:06:02.000
And again, the next thing is to clarify the experience of the interlocutor.

01:06:02.000 --> 01:06:04.000
What is the connection of this statement?

01:06:04.000 --> 01:06:07.000
Maybe you have met only such men?

01:06:07.000 --> 01:06:14.000
Maybe your experience is limited only by them?

01:06:14.000 --> 01:06:17.000
Maybe you have based only on your experience,

01:06:17.000 --> 01:06:19.000
or this experience of someone else?

01:06:19.000 --> 01:06:22.000
The task is to work with universal quantities,

01:06:22.000 --> 01:06:24.000
but I emphasize it again, carefully,

01:06:24.000 --> 01:06:27.000
because it is not worth asking provocative questions here,

01:06:27.000 --> 01:06:29.000
just because maybe the status is not the same.

01:06:29.000 --> 01:06:31.000
You came to negotiations,

01:06:31.000 --> 01:06:34.000
you wanted to learn the contract,

01:06:34.000 --> 01:06:37.000
why should you aggravate the situation?

01:06:37.000 --> 01:06:39.000
Translate the conversation into a neutral topic.

01:06:39.000 --> 01:06:42.000
So, as for the universal quantities,

01:06:42.000 --> 01:06:47.000
then, accordingly, all this is a kind of generalization.

01:06:47.000 --> 01:06:49.000
With the help of our sensory senses,

01:06:49.000 --> 01:06:51.000
vision, hearing, kinesthetics,

01:06:51.000 --> 01:06:55.000
we never have a relationship with the universal quantities.

01:06:55.000 --> 01:06:58.000
We have no relationship with the whole world.

01:06:58.000 --> 01:07:02.000
We have a relationship with a specific room where we are,

01:07:02.000 --> 01:07:04.000
with a specific place where we sit.

01:07:04.000 --> 01:07:12.000
The next element that prevents the formation of an adequate impression

01:07:12.000 --> 01:07:16.000
is the use of comparisons.

01:07:16.000 --> 01:07:19.000
And very often, comparisons with silence,

01:07:19.000 --> 01:07:22.000
when there is no comparison standard.

01:07:22.000 --> 01:07:25.000
In this situation,

01:07:25.000 --> 01:07:30.000
a certain comparison is simply used,

01:07:30.000 --> 01:07:32.000
but it is omitted, what is compared with.

01:07:32.000 --> 01:07:36.000
For example, things are going well,

01:07:36.000 --> 01:07:39.000
we do not need to sign a contract with you.

01:07:39.000 --> 01:07:44.000
What is it, things are going well?

01:07:44.000 --> 01:07:46.000
It is not clear what is being compared with.

01:07:46.000 --> 01:07:49.000
Things are going well compared to what?

01:07:49.000 --> 01:07:51.000
To your previous business,

01:07:51.000 --> 01:07:53.000
to your business with other suppliers,

01:07:53.000 --> 01:07:58.000
to the business that occurs in my personal life.

01:07:58.000 --> 01:08:00.000
What am I comparing with?

01:08:00.000 --> 01:08:02.000
I need to identify this standard.

01:08:02.000 --> 01:08:06.000
Because comparison is pointless.

01:08:06.000 --> 01:08:10.000
I always compare certain circumstances that occur to me

01:08:10.000 --> 01:08:13.000
and strive to deal with these circumstances.

01:08:14.000 --> 01:08:18.000
I will get too little profit from your contract.

01:08:18.000 --> 01:08:20.000
What is too little profit?

01:08:20.000 --> 01:08:22.000
Let's say,

01:08:22.000 --> 01:08:24.000
too little profit of 1%

01:08:24.000 --> 01:08:28.000
means an additional profit of 1.5 million dollars.

01:08:28.000 --> 01:08:30.000
1.5 million dollars is not a significant profit for you.

01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:32.000
We work with different numbers.

01:08:32.000 --> 01:08:36.000
And accordingly, I do not understand what you are comparing with.

01:08:36.000 --> 01:08:39.000
Well, if 1.5 million is not a significant profit for you,

01:08:39.000 --> 01:08:40.000
it is clear.

01:08:40.000 --> 01:08:44.000
But if it is about 1%, what is 1% worth?

01:08:44.000 --> 01:08:46.000
We clarify, and then we already

01:08:46.000 --> 01:08:51.000
start to get to the specifics of the relative comparison.

01:08:51.000 --> 01:08:54.000
And accordingly, 1% is not enough.

01:08:54.000 --> 01:08:56.000
Okay, 2%, 3 million dollars.

01:08:56.000 --> 01:08:58.000
This is a sufficient amount.

01:08:58.000 --> 01:09:02.000
We find common figures from which we can start.

01:09:02.000 --> 01:09:04.000
If 1.5 million is not money for you,

01:09:04.000 --> 01:09:05.000
it is money for me.

01:09:05.000 --> 01:09:11.000
Let's clarify what you benefit from us and what we benefit from you.

01:09:11.000 --> 01:09:18.000
Again, our goal when we work on impressions is to bring the general point of view.

01:09:18.000 --> 01:09:23.000
Our profit is higher than you offer.

01:09:23.000 --> 01:09:25.000
Higher than what?

01:09:25.000 --> 01:09:28.000
Higher than what is your profit and when is it higher?

01:09:28.000 --> 01:09:30.000
Now? And what will happen tomorrow?

01:09:30.000 --> 01:09:36.000
How can the profit change if we use one or another contract?

01:09:36.000 --> 01:09:38.000
Let's say so.

01:09:38.000 --> 01:09:46.000
Or another statement that this company is more generous to dividends than you are.

01:09:46.000 --> 01:09:48.000
More generous to dividends.

01:09:48.000 --> 01:09:51.000
What is it more generous to dividends?

01:09:51.000 --> 01:09:54.000
Then what profit does this company promise?

01:09:54.000 --> 01:09:55.000
Dividends from what?

01:09:55.000 --> 01:09:57.000
From 1.5 million to 500 thousand.

01:09:57.000 --> 01:10:01.000
Again, we are trying to avoid the lack of specifics,

01:10:01.000 --> 01:10:03.000
avoid misunderstanding the situation

01:10:03.000 --> 01:10:08.000
and to move on to the specific figures that we can discuss.

01:10:08.000 --> 01:10:17.000
This is what concerns the impressions that arise with social perception,

01:10:17.000 --> 01:10:19.000
with social interaction,

01:10:19.000 --> 01:10:23.000
which very often arise during the negotiating processes that we conduct.

01:10:24.000 --> 01:10:33.000
Naturally, in this case, the main problem is that we have to verbally clarify what is meant.

01:10:33.000 --> 01:10:39.000
It is pointless to give a lot of arguments to dispel all your doubts.

01:10:39.000 --> 01:10:41.000
All doubts will not be dispelled.

01:10:41.000 --> 01:10:45.000
All, in the end, is also a universal quantity.

01:10:45.000 --> 01:10:50.000
But if I know exactly what I want to figure out,

01:10:50.000 --> 01:10:53.000
what you doubt,

01:10:53.000 --> 01:10:55.000
then we can talk specifically.

01:10:55.000 --> 01:10:58.000
And if we talk specifically, then we already speak a specific language,

01:10:58.000 --> 01:11:00.000
and then we can vary the figures,

01:11:00.000 --> 01:11:01.000
vary the agreements.

01:11:01.000 --> 01:11:07.000
We can form an impression that both parties want

01:11:07.000 --> 01:11:10.000
and, accordingly, get the desired data,

01:11:10.000 --> 01:11:14.000
conclude a particular contract.

01:11:14.000 --> 01:11:18.000
This is what concerns the issue of forming impressions,

01:11:18.000 --> 01:11:22.000
what concerns working with language, with clarification,

01:11:22.000 --> 01:11:28.000
and with the fulfillment of information lost by generalization,

01:11:28.000 --> 01:11:30.000
exclusion and omission.

01:11:37.000 --> 01:11:45.000
I want to draw your attention to the fact that perception is the initial stage of information processing.

01:11:45.000 --> 01:11:50.000
But this is the stage that determines all subsequent methods of work,

01:11:50.000 --> 01:11:55.000
all subsequent results that we will achieve, that we will receive.

01:11:55.000 --> 01:11:59.000
That is why we have devoted so much time to perception,

01:11:59.000 --> 01:12:09.000
and, accordingly, I would like to focus on the most frequent aspects of this perception

01:12:09.000 --> 01:12:13.000
and the formation of the impression that is obtained as a result.

01:12:13.000 --> 01:12:14.000
Thank you for your attention.
